---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Stux OS">
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Stux OS</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Run your own AI operating system.</p>
    <p class="pitch">
      Stux OS is a new kind of operating layer for the age of AI agents. It gives you
      one place to plug in different models and tools, wrap them in clear boundaries,
      and put them to work on the projects that actually matter to you.
    </p>
    <p class="pitch">
      No more scattered prompts and half-remembered chats. Stux helps your assistants
      feel like part of a stable environment, not just another tab.
    </p>
    <div class="cta">
      <a href="/daemon" class="btn primary">Meet the DaemonCore Kernel</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="features">
    <h2 class="section-title">Why Stux OS?</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      AI has moved fast. The systems around it haven't. Most people now juggle multiple
      models, tools, and browser tabs just to get simple work done. Stux OS is the
      missing layer that turns all of that into something coherent.
    </p>
    <div class="feature-grid">
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>One Home for Your Agents</h3>
        <p>
          Bring different AI providers and tools together under a single way of working.
          Swap models in and out without rebuilding your entire setup from scratch.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Predictable Behaviour</h3>
        <p>
          Stux focuses on repeatability. The goal is simple: the same inputs and
          context should lead to the same kind of output, regardless of which
          underlying model you're using.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Human-Controlled by Design</h3>
        <p>
          Stux is built around human oversight. You decide what agents are there to
          do and how much freedom they get. They work inside your rules – not the
          other way around.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="components">
    <h2 class="section-title">The Stux Platform</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      Stux OS will grow over time. The first building block is DaemonCore – a kernel
      that keeps agents organised, on-task, and inside clear boundaries.
    </p>
    <div class="component-grid">
      <a href="/daemon" class="component-card">
        <h3>DaemonCore</h3>
        <p>
          The core kernel behind Stux OS. It gives agents a structured way to start up,
          understand where they are, and stay aligned with your priorities.
        </p>
        <span class="badge active">In Active Development</span>
      </a>
      <div class="component-card coming-soon">
        <h3>Stux SDK</h3>
        <p>
          Developer tooling for wiring existing apps, automations, and workflows into
          the Stux way of working – without throwing anything away.
        </p>
        <span class="badge">Coming Soon</span>
      </div>
      <div class="component-card coming-soon">
        <h3>Stux Hub</h3>
        <p>
          A future control centre for managing agent setups, profiles, and installations
          across machines, teams, and environments.
        </p>
        <span class="badge">Coming Soon</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="status">
    <h2>Status</h2>
    <p>
      Stux OS is an early-stage project. The current focus is on proving and hardening
      the DaemonCore kernel in real-world use, then opening up a clear path for
      developers and teams who want to run AI on their own terms.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 6rem 0 4rem;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-size: 4rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .pitch {
    max-width: 650px;
    margin: 0 auto 1.25rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .cta {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .btn {
    padding: 0.875rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 1rem;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .btn.primary {
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: white;
  }

  .btn.primary:hover {
    background: var(--color-accent-hover);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }

  .features {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .section-intro {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .feature-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .feature {
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .feature h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .feature p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .components {
    padding: 4rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .component-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .component-card {
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    position: relative;
  }

  .component-card:hover:not(.coming-soon) {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .component-card.coming-soon {
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .component-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .component-card p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .badge {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .badge.active {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .status {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 4rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .status p {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }

    .subtitle {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
